  Save it (Ctrl+S). If you actually want to commit the pretrained yolov8n.pt / yolov8n-seg.pt (they're ~6 MB each, GitHub-safe), remove the
  *.pt line — but I'd recommend keeping it out and downloading weights on demand.

  3. Initialize the repo (two equivalent ways)

  Way A — via Source Control panel (the one you mentioned):

  - Click the branch-shaped icon on the left activity bar (Ctrl + Shift + G, then G).
  - The panel will say "The folder currently open doesn't have a git repository." Click the Initialize Repository button.
  - The panel now shows all files under "Changes". Files matching .gitignore are hidden.

  Way B — via terminal: git init. Same effect.

  4. First commit — via the Source Control panel

  - In the Source Control panel, hover any file under "Changes" → click the + (Stage Changes) icon. To stage everything at once, hover the
  "Changes" header and click the + there.
  - Type a commit message in the box at the top — e.g. Initial commit — multi-pipeline auto-labeller.
